The paper presents a network architecture for processing point clouds, which involves using convolutional layers on a high-dimensional lattice. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of spatially-aware feature learning and joint 2D-3D reasoning, which could also indicate a potential fit for the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the incorporation of point-based and image-based representations, which could suggest a fit for the natural language processing (cs.CL) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
